{"id":"2009.12937","submitter":"Sayan Banerjee","authors":"Sayan Banerjee, Brendan Brown","title":"Dimension-free local convergence and perturbations for reflected\n  Brownian motions","comments":"40 pages. To appear in Ann. Appl. Probab","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.PR","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We describe and analyze a class of positive recurrent reflected Brownian\nmotions (RBMs) in $\\mathbb{R}^d_+$ for which local statistics converge to\nequilibrium at a rate independent of the dimension $d$. Under suitable\nassumptions on the reflection matrix, drift and diffusivity coefficients,\ndimension-independent stretched exponential convergence rates are obtained by\nestimating contractions in an underlying weighted distance between\nsynchronously coupled RBMs. We also study the Symmetric Atlas model as a first\nstep in obtaining dimension-independent convergence rates for RBMs not\nsatisfying the above assumptions. By analyzing a pathwise derivative process\nand connecting it to a random walk in a random environment, we obtain\npolynomial convergence rates for the gap process of the Symmetric Atlas model\nstarted from appropriate perturbations of stationarity.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 27 Sep 2020 20:20:36 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 2 Oct 2020 21:19:21 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 21 Mar 2022 22:19:46 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-03-23"}
